content: Dear renju friends,Good evening! I am Zhang Jinyu from China. Thanks ando and Renjuclass for giving me such an opportunity to have the presentation.
We are happy to have you teach here :)
I know there are many good players here. Ando had said teaching is also learning. I hope I can learn something from you.
First, I'd like say something on Chinese renju.
As you know, Na Wei is the first people who introduce renju into china. He made the first renju club about 10 years ago.
At that time, ando got his first world champion but still there are not strong Chinese players at that time, even do not know how to win in I7 and D4 opening.
After so many years development, many Chinese renju clubs are set up and Chinese players become much stronger.

But because Chinese players lack opportunity to join the international tournament, their strengths are not fully recognized by other countries' players. And also lacking international tournament experience hinders them growth up.
They need tough training in international tournament.
Mainly because of lacking money, the most frequently renju activities are doing on internet.
Hi, Zhang, will you remember me who stayed  on Xihai group?
there are still many Chinese players studying renju. Most of renjuclass students are come from China.

There are also many Chinese renju websites such as www.basecity.com, www.ourgame.com or www.263.com and so on. You can find thousands of Chinese playing renju on these websites everyday.There are also many Chinese renju websites such as www.basecity.com, www.ourgame.com or www.263.com and so on. You can find thousands of Chinese playing renju on these websites everyday.
aha,GM's English is not as good as his Renju :)
Many Chinese players also join the e-mail tournament every year. They show quite high level and there are 4 players in A tournament now.
In old days, e-mail tournament is dominated by Russia players. Now the situation began to change.
Ando had made many excellent presentation on many real games.
In the presentation, I'd like to talk about something on e-mail tournament and some of my ideas on renju.
That's great! Look forwatd to them :)
I know some of you join the e-mail tournament. E-mail tournament is quite different from real tournament.
But because the game is quite slow and lack the stimulating feeling as playing face to face, not all the players like such style.
Any way it attracts many strong players join the tournament such as ando, tunnet, ants, Reims, Kawamura, Hesengawa and most of Russia renju players.
In the presentation, i will not do many detail analysis on the game. The class will be quite relax and just like chat.
If you have any question, please feel free to propose.
yong fan yi ruanjian lai fanyi zhe kan :)
in e-mail tournament, your opponent has enough time to analysis a pattern. It is almost impossible to count on his simple mistakes to win a game.
You may have quite different feeling in real game and e-mail tournament. In e-mail tournament, some plain pattern may have very strong attack, and some patter with great advantage but no win.
very hard to win in email games
Some popular patterns are shown sure lost and some used patterns are picked up and become popular.
Playing in the tournament, I think one must pay attention to two important factors: one is opening choice, the other is calculation. It looks quite simple but is not easily be used in the games.
Let us first clarify some simple concepts before discussing the problem. And we will discuss the difference between real game and e-mail games.
When we analysis a pattern, there may be some situations:
most hardest to choose opening patterm, harder than playing the game :)))

But the true things is that We experience a no win feeling in most of cases.

So, you must controll your attack, and aware win or not win in very early time
As you know, renju opening is quite complicated. No one can analysis to the end from the beginning. Most of us always choose a known theory and play.
But not all the people copy the theory from the beginning to the end, Changing always happens.
he new moves always break the balance and bring win or lose. We must pay much attention to your opponent's new moves or idea.
We must have an intuition to know which pattern is safety, which pattern may have problems.
It is very hard. Maybe you need many training to have the feeling. Only repeating old theory may cause disasters.
Even the players in group A can not do it well.
I will give you some examples on the subject.
The game from bobkov and me he made the opening.
I was suprised but I found his idea from database.
He played many games in the pattern.
He should expect me to play like that. And make perfect defense.
Catch me when my attack fails.
to be honest, I do not think it is a win pattern. If I play so, I will fall into his opening trap.
Of course, all of this comes from detail calculation.
But for I had anticipate this, I must do something.
But to me suprise, he made an odd defense.
I think he is very strong and this is the only correct defense.
I go on set pressure to him and hope he made mistake.
but his 20 is a fatal mistake.
The game over. No win for white, and no defense
16 strange defense, if it is not a VCT threat at least
In e-mail game, you can see many odd defense and attack. It totally defends on calculalation.

To win a game, you must make very precise attack and defense.
You must anticiplate your opponents' idea in very early time and catch him by some new move.
Do not expect you opponent will make foolish mistakes.
